   The Assistant Secretary for Planning and Evaluation (ASPE) is the
   principal advisor to the Secretary of the U.S. Department of Health and
   Human Services on policy development, and is responsible for major
   activities in the areas of policy coordination, legislation
   development, strategic planning, policy research and evaluation, and
   economic analysis.
